Retired President Mwai Kibaki's body arrived at parliament buildings earlier this morning under tight security. The retired President Kibaki's body will lie in state from Monday to Wednesday. During this time, the public will be allowed to view the body ahead of the State Funeral on Friday at Nyayo Stadium. President Uhuru Kenyatta and First Lady Margaret Kenyatta led the nation in paying tributes to the late President. Kibaki died on Friday at the age of 90. He will be buried on Saturday.